# **About the freeDSPx AMP x4** {#about-the-freedspx-amp-x4}

The freeDSPx AMP x4 is a four channel amplifier module with a digital eight channel TDM input, designed to be used with a freeDSP module. The freeDSPx AMP x4 is a medium power class-D amplifier based on the TAS5720M IC from Texas Instruments and can supply up to 25 Watts with less than 1% THD+N to a 4Ω load per channel. The amplifier directly uses a digital input signal and circumvents an additional digital to analog conversion after the DSP. Overall noise and signal to noise ratio will be improved through that. Two freeDSPx AMP x4 can be stacked to form an eight channel amplifier.

Further increase in the supply voltage up to 26,4 V is possible but will not lead to more output power. The output power of the freeDSPx AMP x4 is shown in Table 1\.

## **Digital input** {#digital-input}

The freeDSPx AMP x4 features an digital eight channel time division multiplexed (TDM) input. The amplifier can use the lower (0-3) or upper (4-7) four slots of a TDM-8 frame as input. The input slots can be selected with the TDM slot jumper. You can use a ribbon cable and crimp multiple connectors on it, to connect two freeDSPx AMP x4 to a single TDM output of a freeDSP and amplify all eight channels. 

For more details on TDM and digital audio communication with the freeDSP system refer to the freeDSP \- serial audio getting started guide.

## **LEDs and fault states**  {#leds-and-fault-states}

The freeDSPx AMP x4 has a green power led (D4) which indicates that the amplifier is powered. The module also has four red fault leds (D5, D6, D7, D8) which indicate a fault state on the closest amplifier IC to the led. Reasons for faults  states can be:

1) no correct digital TDM signal at the input  
2) overtemperature of the amplifier IC  
3) overcurrent or short circuit at the output  
4) over- or undervoltage at the power supply  

When a fault state occurs the amplifier will mute the corresponding output. The output will be automatically unmuted pop-free after the fault state is no longer present.

If you group together with friends or others and order pbs and components in bulk, you can save money. 

## **Solder the board**  {#solder-the-board}

All surface mounted devices of the freeDSPx AMP x4 have to be soldered in a reflow process. The solder paste should be stencil printed. The manufacturing data for a stencil is also available on the freeDSP GitHub. Keep in mind that the TAS5720M amplifier IC is a fine-pitch component in a QFN package with 0,4 mm pitch and will require sufficient precision in the manufacturing process.

All through hole components of the freeDSPx AMP x4 can be hand soldered after the reflow process.

If you can not reflow solder the amplifier on your own you can order it from a professional manufacturer of your choice. If you group together with others for this and order a larger quantity you can save a lot of money.

The freeDSPx AMP x4 has to be connected to a freeDSP module with a I²S standard connector and a TDM output. A freeDSP Classic DSP with a freeDSPx-Adapter can also be used. The freeDSPx AMP x4 is compatible to a 12.288 MHz or 24.576 MHz masterclock.
